visual.name: BoxWhisker(JanPieter)
visual.description: Visualize a dataset as a box and whisker chart. A box and whisker chart shows basic statistical information of a dataset: the 1st and 3rd quartile (box),  the median (line), the mean (dot) and dependent of the type either the minimum and maximum value of all values or between the 1.5x interquartile range [IQR] (whiskers).

orientation.description: Orientation of the chart, horizontal or viertical

quartile.description: The way of how the quartiles are calculated, inclusive or exclusive

includeEmpty.description: Treat empty values as zeros (0) in calculations

margin.description:
The margin between the different boxes.
Only used when no datalabels are shown

labelPrecision.description: Select the number of decimal places to display

orientation.description: Set the orientation of the labels

labelPrecision.description: Select the number of decimal places to display

toolTip.description: Settings used for the default tooltips.

labelPrecision.description: Select the number of decimal places to display

fontSize.description: If datalabels are to big, the default size is used.

labelPrecision.description: Select the number of decimal places to display

fixedCategory.description: When highlight is not supported, keep the same amount of categories

dataLoad.description: Settings related to loading large datasets

enablePaging.description: Enable loading of more data points then +/- 30.000 rows

showProgress.description: Show message when additional data loading is in progress

progressText.description: Text of the data loading progress

showWarning.description: Show warning if there is more data available, but not loaded

position.description: Arrange relative to chart data points

labelPrecision.description: Select the number of decimal places to display
